  <figcaption>
    Biochar production produces a lot of heat, and most stand-alone biochar reactors simple release their heat into the atmosphere. By co-locating ours next to the ethanol distillation unit we are able to capture and use (cogenerate) all of that heat needed to fuel the ethanol production process. This eliminates an operating cost, thus helping to “close the loop” both economically and environmentally.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<figure>
